Backport upstream fix for LLVM bug #40712 to LLVM 7.x.

Without explicit member initializers, MSVC does not treat the
defaulted ManagedStaticBase constructor as constexpr, so the
`AllSubCommands` ManagedStatic gets dynamic initialization that
runs after every `cl::opt` static initializer — wiping the option
list it was supposed to back. Result on modern MSVC: every cl::opt
registered via cl::sub(*AllSubCommands) (i.e. -help, all of
TableGen's -gen-* actions) silently disappears at runtime; only
options not routed through ManagedStatic (-color, --version)
survive. Linkers and link-time flags cannot work around this; the
bug is in C++ initialization order.

The MSVC STL's older internal workaround that masked this is gone
as of recent VS 2019 / 2022 toolsets, which is why the previous
LLVM 7 Windows tarball (built years ago) worked but rebuilds today
do not.

Upstream fix:   https://reviews.llvm.org/D80433
Upstream issue: https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/40712

--- a/include/llvm/Support/ManagedStatic.h
+++ b/include/llvm/Support/ManagedStatic.h
@@ -38,9 +38,9 @@
 protected:
   // This should only be used as a static variable, which guarantees that this
   // will be zero initialized.
-  mutable std::atomic<void *> Ptr;
-  mutable void (*DeleterFn)(void*);
-  mutable const ManagedStaticBase *Next;
+  mutable std::atomic<void *> Ptr{nullptr};
+  mutable void (*DeleterFn)(void*) = nullptr;
+  mutable const ManagedStaticBase *Next = nullptr;
 
   void RegisterManagedStatic(void *(*creator)(), void (*deleter)(void*)) const;
 
